{"tid":1200794,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"美國國會議員再致函林鄭：要求撤回條例","createTime":"2019-06-10T23:31:46.000Z","updateTime":"2019-06-11T11:02:10.000Z","uid":41404,"like":49,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"5c9194d947b004724285200eb4df89e15c0fcff1","tid":1200794,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-10T23:31:46.000Z","msg":"China Commission<br />\n@CECCgov<br />\nWe stand w/the people of #HongKong. Their peaceful demonstrations are a strong &amp; profound statement against the extradition bill, which undermines the rule of law &amp; a secure business environment. We urge Chief Executive Carrie Lam to withdraw the bill. (link: <a href=\"https://go.usa.gov/xmzFx\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgo.usa.gov%2FxmzFx&d=bDeBUyUVyPRGeZhx3zx6lWaNvfBTe1ydx6p2nKz01sw%3D&h=838d58a5\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://go.usa.gov/xmzFx</a>) <a href=\"http://go.usa.gov/xmzFx\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgo.usa.gov%2FxmzFx&d=bDeBUyUVyPRGeZhx3zx6lWaNvfBTe1ydx6p2nKz01sw%3D&h=6a289563\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">go.usa.gov/xmzFx</a>"},{"pid":"34bdf4914d6129fe5d3423f22735a310b63c148c","tid":1200794,"uid":41404,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-06-10T23:32:34.000Z","msg":"(Washington D.C.)&mdash;U.S. Representative James P. McGovern (D-MA) and U.S. Senator Marco Rubio (R-FL), the chair and cochair respectively of the bipartisan and bicameral Congressional-Executive Commission on China (CECC), sent a letter yesterday to Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam expressing &ldquo;concern&rdquo; that proposed amendments to Hong Kong&rsquo;s extradition law would &ldquo;negatively impact the relationship between the United States and Hong Kong&rdquo; and asked that the amendments be &ldquo;withdrawn from consideration.&rdquo;  Full text of the letter can be found here. <br />\nThe CECC Chairs were joined by a bipartisan group of CECC Commissioners including Sen